Samsung Galaxy A51 (Prism Crush Blue, 128 GB, 6 GB RAM)
Review Detail: Purchased this model 3 weeks back. Here's my impressions so far Positives:  Sleek appealing design with thinner bezels.  Display is awesome and viewing content is a treat to watch. Camera is pretty good.  Though 60Hz refresh rate, it's smooth to navigate between apps or pages. Case and earphones bundled with box is appreciable.  Not so good stuffs The charger wire length is too small and is a pain to connect for charging the phone. Battery is pretty average with roughly 22hr battery life I am getting on average.  Performance (processor) is not the strong point of this phone, but for my usage and for most of common man's usage, this will suffice.  All in all will give 4 out of 5.  P.S: Came to purchase A52, ended up buying A51 as A52 wasn't on display and buying A51 made me feel a better value for money. Saved around 6k, plus case and earphone included. With 5G variant being the future I am happy not spending extra money for a costlier 4G variant A52. Maybe an A52 5G would have tempted me to go for it.  Anyways happy with A51.
